The paper discusses a neural network architecture for question answering, which falls under the field of natural language processing (NLP). The use of a memory network and focus attention mechanism suggests a focus on deep learning techniques, which are commonly used in subfields such as computational linguistics (cs.CL), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and machine learning (cs.LG). The experiments involve both synthetic and real datasets, indicating a broad scope of application, which could also suggest computer vision (cs.CV) and neural engineering (cs.NE) as potential subfields.
